---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About - naimul.net" description="About the writer behind naimul.net.">
  <section class="container page-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
    <h1 class="page-title">A place for paying attention.</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      This blog is a home for essays, reading notes, photographs, and travel logs. The tone is simple:
      notice more, keep what matters, and publish without making the internet louder than it needs to be.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="container section split">
    <div>
      <img
        class="article-image"
        src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1518005020951-eccb494ad742?auto=format&fit=crop&w=1000&q=80"
        alt="A quiet desk with warm light and notebooks"
      />
    </div>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        I write about what I am learning, what I am reading, and what I notice when I step away from the screen.
        Some posts are practical. Some are reflective. Some are just a record of a walk, a photograph, or a page
        that stayed with me.
      </p>
      <p>
        The site is intentionally minimal: fast pages, readable typography, natural colors, and no unnecessary
        clutter between the reader and the piece.
      </p>
      <p>
        The main sections are reading, photography, hiking, travel, and personal essays. Over time, this becomes
        an archive of attention.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
